name: history-lens
display_name: History Lens
version: 1.0.0
author: Rajdeep Pandhare
repository: CLAUDE-SKILLS
license: MIT
description: >
  A decision analysis engine that routes a decision to 1-2 matched company
  archetypes, surfaces the specific historical analog and the structural
  enabler that made it work for that company, strips it to a transferable
  principle re-derived under the user's actual constraints, forces explicit
  disagreement between matched lenses to surface the real tradeoff, and
  attaches a graveyard countercase per archetype to counter survivorship bias.

entry_point: SKILL.md

triggers:
  - "what would X do"
  - "how would Amazon approach this"
  - "what would Apple do"
  - "what would Stripe do"
  - "what would history do"
  - "learn from companies"
  - "how did great companies decide"
  - "what would a great company do"
  - "decision archetype"
  - "historical analog"
  - "pressure-test this decision"

references:
  - path: references/amazon.md
    archetype: Amazon
    core_muscle: Long-horizon bet under public scrutiny and margin pressure
  - path: references/apple.md
    archetype: Apple
    core_muscle: Ruthless prioritization — saying no as a strategic capability
  - path: references/microsoft.md
    archetype: Microsoft
    core_muscle: Platform/ecosystem leverage — becoming infrastructure inside other people's stacks
  - path: references/nvidia.md
    archetype: Nvidia
    core_muscle: Betting on a thesis before the market agrees
  - path: references/stripe.md
    archetype: Stripe
    core_muscle: Default infrastructure via developer obsession

pipeline:
  phases:
    - id: 1
      name: Decision Intake
      goal: Lock in the concrete committed decision and its constraints before selecting any lens
    - id: 2
      name: Archetype Matching
      goal: Select 1-2 genuinely relevant archetypes; never run all five
    - id: 3
      name: Lens Analysis
      goal: Historical analog, structural enabler, transferable principle, and mandatory graveyard countercase per matched archetype
    - id: 4
      name: Lens Disagreement
      goal: Surface contradictory recommendations between matched lenses without resolving them
    - id: 5
      name: Constraint Re-derivation
      goal: Re-derive each transferable principle under the user's actual constraints
    - id: 6
      name: Recommendation
      goal: Single concrete recommendation plus mandatory Decision Audit handoff block

guardrails:
  - Never skip Layer 1 (historical analog) or Layer 2 (structural enabler) to jump to the transferable principle
  - Never omit the graveyard countercase for a matched archetype
  - Never run more than two lenses per decision
  - Never resolve lens disagreement by declaring a winner
  - Never deliver a recommendation that is not re-derived from the user's stated constraints
  - Always output the Decision Audit handoff block

output_format: markdown

compatible_with:
  - claude.ai
  - claude-code

tags:
  - decision-making
  - strategy
  - business-analysis
  - mental-models
